<TITLE> RAB takes Niki into two-day remand </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 21 (bdnews24.com)  RAB Wednesday took alleged Yaba trader Jannatul Ferdous Niki into a two-day remand in custody for interrogation. Dhaka metropolitan magistrate Shanaz Sultana ordered her into remand in the afternoon. RAB-3 sub-inspector Selim Badsha appealed for three-day remand in a case that charges Niki with possession of 34 pieces of the banned drug at her Karnaphuli Garden City home. RAB officer Khairul Hasan filed a narcotics case against Niki with Ramna Police Station on Nov 4 after she was arrested the same day. The law enforcers also arrested Niki's boyfriend Mahbubur Rahman Joynal, managing director of Hotel Purbani International on Nov 4. He is now in jail. Niki's father Abdur Noor, mother Saleha Begum and brother Mohiuddin were also arrested and sent to jail on Nov 12 in connection with the case. They had also been remanded for three days. On information they gave during interrogation, law enforcers seized a large quantity of Yaba and narcotics from different areas in the city. bdne
